<br>
Magicians (54 and under) trying to lead a pick-up type PoH raid and defaulting the earth staff.  Now I realize all the magicians want one for epic (me included) and this seems to be the best idea to get one.  Be the raid leader and default 1 item to yourself.<br>
<br>
However, let us look at the result of such an action.  If the staff is defaulted, I have no reason to join in such an effort.  Nor does any other magician.  I go to places and do things for guildmates and friends who need epic items often enough as it is, I have no reason to join a raid lead by somebody only to be excluded from the one item I need.<br>
<br>
So let's say the leader is the only magician now.  And he is level 52 for example.<br>
<br>
(1)  I normally give the monk puller a Gift of Xev bag full of summoned shurikens (L55 spell).<br>
(2)  I normally make focus items for everyone.  The most important one being the DD bracer (L54 spell).<br>
(3)  I am normally in the pull group for CoH (L55 spell).<br>
(4)  I normally do the DS on the MA with Cadeau of flame (L56 spell).<br>
(5)  I provide the T-rods for clerics and main enchanter/slower (L56 spell)<br>
(6)  Because of my level, I can often nuke for high damage vs. most mobs in Hate.<br>
(7)  On multi-mob pulls, I can malosini the extras to make it easier on the enchanter mezzing.<br>
(8)  On the high MR mobs, I can use Rage of Zoom (L55 spell)<br>
<br>
<br>
Now BB has a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.everquestraids.com"> calender</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> that makes it easy to schedule raids for people like me who want to invite outside of guild.  It is not a reservation system, just a nice utility for making raid organization easier.  My raids are usually locked and invite only can join.  However other raids are &quot;open&quot; and anybody can join if they meet the level requirement set by the leader.<br>
<br>
We had a 51 mage try to take every Sunday for 5 weeks straight, each time defaulting the earth staff.  We currently have a 52 magician who put PoH raids up for 5 days in a row (5/6-5/10) with epic defaulted.  <br>
<br>
Now chances are these raids will never happen.  People won't sign up, lack of interest, etc. for a single magician trying to recruit 30+ people to help him.  And frankly, I know I certainly won't be going when they expect the staff to be defaulted.<br>
<br>
/rant off<br>
